myplot <- function(xdata, ydata, title = "", xlm, ylb, col = "black", ylm = c(0, 1)) {
    plot(xdata, ydata,
        type = "l", col = col,
        main = paste(title, ylb), xlab = "X", ylab = ylb,
        xlim = xlm, ylim = ylm
    )
}

par(mfrow = c(1, 1))

estimate <- function() {
    x <- runif(1, 10, 30)
    y <- runif(1, 10, 20)
    if (x > y) {
        return(y * 300)
    } else {
        return(x * 200 + y * 100)
    }
}
try <- 10000
x <- c()
for (i in 1:try) {
    x <- c(x, estimate())
}
mean(x)
## [1] 4339.656

f <- function(x, y, z) {
    return(x * exp(-y^2 + z^2) + x * y * z)
}
times <- 1000
n <- 1000
data = c()
for(i in 1:times) data=c(data,mean(f(runif(n, 3, 6), runif(n, 2, 4), runif(n, 1, 3))))

mean(data * 2 * 2 * 3)
## [1] 404.9739
